==設計==
[[File:Palace_of_Fine_Arts-5.jpg|thumb]]
藝術宮圍繞於一座人工湖，由總長{{convert|1100|ft|m|lk=on}}的蔭徑圍繞著中央的圓形大廳。<ref>{{en}}{{cite web |url=http://www.lib.umd.edu/digital/worldsfairs/record.jsp?pid=umd:1006 |title=Palace of Fine Arts |last=Yu |first=James |work=University of Maryland |deadurl=no |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120415103033/http://digital.lib.umd.edu/worldsfairs/record.jsp?pid=umd:1006 |archivedate=2012-04-15 |accessdate=2014-04-16 }}</ref>人工湖則是仿效歐洲的經典建築，其廣闊的水面像鏡子般地倒映出藝術宮的雄偉，並能從遠處欣賞這寧靜的景色。

裝飾品包括布魯諾·路易斯·齊姆（Bruno Louis Zimm）繪製於圓形大廳頂部的三幅循環油畫，象徵著希臘文化，也表現出「為美麗而奮鬥」的精神。<ref>{{en}}{{cite web |url=http://www.inetours.com/Pages/SFNbrhds/Palace-Fine-Arts.html |title=Palace of Fine Arts, San Francisco Marina Neighborhood |author=Lee W. Nelson |work=INTERNET TOURS |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131001011101/http://www.inetours.com/Pages/SFNbrhds/Palace-Fine-Arts.html |archivedate=2013-10-01 |accessdate=2014-04-16 }}</ref>{{link-en|烏爾里希·埃勒胡森|Ulric Ellerhusen}}於柱廊頂上安置哭泣的女人，並於柱的中楣上雕刻，這些人形雕像象徵著「沉思、驚奇和冥想」。<ref>{{cite book |author=National Sculpture Society |title=Exhibition of American Sculpture Catalogue |location=U.S. |publisher=National Sculpture Society |year=1923 |page=55 |accessdate=2014-04-18 }}</ref><ref name=Macomber>{{cite book  | last =Macomber  | first =Ben  | authorlink =  | title =The Jewel City: Its Planning and Achievement; Its Architecture, Sculpture, Symbolism, and Music; Its Gardens, Palaces, and Exhibits  | publisher =John H. Williams, Publisher  | year =1915  | location =San Francisco and Tacoma  | chapter =The Palace of Fine Arts and its Exhibit, With the Awards  | url =http://www.books-about-california.com/Pages/The_Jewel_City/The_Jewel_City_Chap_12.html  | access-date =2014-04-15  | archive-date =2021-01-12  | archive-url =https://web.archive.org/web/20210112081456/http://www.books-about-california.com/Pages/The_Jewel_City/The_Jewel_City_Chap_12.html  | dead-url =no  }}</ref>

原先，圓形大廳的圓頂底下有著八幅{{link-en|羅伯特·里德 (畫家)|Robert Reid (painter)|羅伯特·里德}}的大型壁畫，其中四幅描繪藝術的概念與誕生，「它奉獻給地球，它藉由人類的智慧而進步且被接受」，另外四幅則是加州的「黃金」（[[罌粟花|罌粟花]]、[[柑橘|柑橘]]、[[黃金|黃金]]和[[小麥|小麥]]）。<ref>{{en}}{{cite web |url=http://www.fullbooks.com/The-Art-of-the-Exposition.html |title=The Art of the Exposition |last=Neuhaus |first=Eugen |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120305194319/http://www.fullbooks.com/The-Art-of-the-Exposition.html |archivedate=2012-03-05 |accessdate=2014-04-16 }}</ref>

==博覽會中其他被保存的建築==
[[File:California_Palace_of_the_Legion_of_Honor,_01.JPG|thumb]]
藝術宮並不是博覽會中唯一被保存下來的建築。日本茶館（並非指1894年加州冬至萬國博覽會於[[金門公園|金門公園]]的[[日本茶園|日本茶園]]）於1915年被當地的男爵E．D．斯威夫特收購，並且以駁船將其從[[舊金山灣區|舊金山灣區]]運輸至位於[[貝爾蒙特_(加利福尼亞州)|貝爾蒙特]]的現址。<ref>{{en}} {{cite web |url=http://www.thevansrestaurant.com/history.htm |title=History of The Vans restaurant |work=The Vans restaurant |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140413150159/http://www.thevansrestaurant.com/history.htm |archivedate=2014-04-13 |accessdate=2014-04-16 }}</ref>[[威斯康辛州|威斯康辛州]]與[[維吉尼亞州|維吉尼亞州]]的展館被重新安置於[[馬林郡|馬林郡]]，[[俄亥俄州|俄亥俄州]]展館則被運送至[[聖馬刁郡|聖馬刁郡]]，並在那一直被保留至1950年代。<ref name="Lipsky">{{cite book |last=Lipsky |first1=William |url=http://books.google.com.tw/books?id=BRFV9H6d0NAC&pg=PA123&dq=0-7385-3009-3&hl=zh-TW&sa=X&ei=s5JQU4qEIcT58QWvz4CYBg&ved=0CDAQ6AEwAA#v=onepage&q=0-7385-3009-3&f=false |title=San Francisco's Panama-Pacific International Exposition |chapter=The End of the Trail |publisher=Arcadia Publishing |year=2005 |page=123 |isbn=978-0738530093 |accessdate=2014-04-18 |archive-date=2014-04-19 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140419081159/http://books.google.com.tw/books?id=BRFV9H6d0NAC&pg=PA123&dq=0-7385-3009-3&hl=zh-TW&sa=X&ei=s5JQU4qEIcT58QWvz4CYBg&ved=0CDAQ6AEwAA#v=onepage&q=0-7385-3009-3&f=false |dead-url=no }}</ref>「進步之柱」（Column of Progress）在博覽會結束後，仍在那佇立了十年，最終，為了疏通濱海大道的交通而被拆除。<ref name="Lipsky"/><ref>{{en}} {{cite web |url=http://foundsf.org/index.php?title=Destruction_of_the_Fair |title=Destruction of the Fair |last=Brechin |first=Gray |work=foundsf.org |deadurl=no |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131014211808/http://www.foundsf.org/index.php?title=Destruction_of_the_Fair |archivedate=2013-10-14 |accessdate=2014-04-18 }}</ref>不建於博覽會場且唯一保留於原址的是舊金山市政禮堂（San Francisco Civic Auditorium），1992年，為了紀念去年墜機身亡的搖滾演唱會經紀人{{link-en|比爾·格雷厄姆|Bill Graham (promoter)}}，重新命名為[[比爾·格雷厄姆市政禮堂|比爾·格雷厄姆市政禮堂]]。<ref>{{en}} {{cite news |author=United Press International |url=http://www.upi.com/Odd_News/2002/10/11/Today-in-Music-a-look-back-at-pop-music/UPI-35331034318700/ |title=Today in Music: a look back at pop music |work=UPI |publisher=UPI |date=2002-10-11 |deadurl=no |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140415041747/http://www.upi.com/Odd_News/2002/10/11/Today-in-Music-a-look-back-at-pop-music/UPI-35331034318700/ |archivedate=2014-04-15 |accessdate=2014-04-16 }}</ref>

位於{{link-en|林肯公園 (舊金山)|Lincoln Park (San Francisco)|林肯公園}}的{{link-en|榮勳宮 (舊金山)|Legion of Honor (museum)|榮勳宮}}是1915年巴拿馬太平洋萬國博覽會中法國館的原尺寸複製品，同時也是被稱為「沙門的別墅」（{{lang-fr|Hôtel de Salm}}）的[[巴黎|巴黎]][[榮勳宮|榮勳宮]]的四分之三比例仿造品。在博覽會結束後，法國政府允許人稱「舊金山曾祖母」的{{link-en|阿爾瑪·德·布雷特維爾·斯普雷克爾斯|Alma de Bretteville Spreckels|阿爾瑪·斯普雷克爾斯}}建造法國館的永久複製品，但是[[第一次世界大战|第一次世界大战]]拖延了施工進度，直到1921年才破土。<ref>{{en}}  {{cite web |url=https://legionofhonor.famsf.org/about/history-legion-honor |title=History of the Legion of Honor |work=Fine Arts Museums of San Francisco |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130912061301/http://legionofhonor.famsf.org/about/history-legion-honor |archivedate=2013-09-12 |accessdate=2014-04-16 }}</ref>

